# Verification protocol

- For bug fixes, reproduce the failure first when feasible and add a regression test.
- Never delete, skip, weaken, or rewrite a valid test just to make implementation pass.
- Run targeted checks first, then every mandatory project check applicable to the change.
- Verify behavior through actual execution when possible; syntax and code inspection alone are insufficient.
- Review the final diff against the original request and acceptance criteria.
- For substantial changes, use a fresh context or read-only subagent to review the diff, requirements, and real verification output.
- Maximum repair attempts for the same failing check: 3. If the same check fails twice without meaningful progress, reassess or escalate instead of repeating the same approach.
- Do not declare completion while a mandatory check is failed, skipped, or unknown.
